    "John H. Walton, John K. Riches": "),assumed leadership. When\nDavid `[char_David_Rut_4]` steps 119 1 Samuel 17\nTeaching the Text Illustrating the Text 1 Samuel 18 Big Idea The\nLord protects and grants success to his chosen servants.\nUnderstanding the Text\nThe Text in Context Historical and Cultural Background Key\nThemes of 1 Samuel 18 Interpretive Insights He was prophesying\ufffd\nWe might be tempted to think of prophesying in a posi\n17:37 The Lord \ufffd \ufffd \ufffd will rescue me\ufffd David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s declaration echoes\nthe speeches of Samuel, who on two occasions reminded the people\nhow the Lord is able to deliver them from the hand of their enemies\n[v_1Sa_7_3] (1 Sam. 7:3; 10:18).\nv. 37), and he has a more creative plan in mind for\ndefeating Goliath."
